@Node robinr "Robin Evans"

Mr. (as in Robin Hood, in case you were wondering) Evans has, in his
checkered past, sprayed asbestos onto the ceilings of mobile homes and
designed databases for lawyers (two activities that seem somehow
related). Between those periods, he edited a biweekly community
newspaper in Seattle and typeset enough headlines and stories on a
CompuGraphic EditWriter 7500 to realize that computers could be nifty
things after all.

He was a serious enough philosophy major in college (a time when he
thought that computers just might be evil) that he can still give a
passable definition of "epistomology" or "ontology."

He moved up from a C-64 to his first Amiga (a 500) in 1988 and bought
ARexx shortly thereafter. When he discovered what could be done with
ARexx by itself and ARexx with TxEd, he was hooked.

Evans recently release ARexxGuide, a complete shareware reference and
tutorial to ARexx in AmigaGuide format. It is available in the GEnie
libraries under the name ARexxGuide1_0.lha.

He'll be teaching an introductory @{"class" link calc} in ARexx programming this fall in
CALC, GEnie's online community college.

@EndNode

