@node calc

If you've been hoping to learn ARexx programming, but haven't had the time,
this may be your chance. GEnie will offer a class on ARexx during the 1993
fall term. The author of ARexxGuide (Robin Evans) will offer classroom
guidance and individual help to students.

(Note: The fall term is underway; contact CALC administration for details
concerning future REXX/AREXX courses.)

The shareware fee for ARexxGuide will be waived for those who register for
the fall course.

COURSE DESCRIPTION:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Title: INTRODUCTION TO REXX/AREXX PROGRAMMING
Section Number: CSE 318

Students in this course will learn the fundamentals of the REXX
programming/macro language which was developed for IBM mainframes and is
now available for several desktop computers, notably PCs running OS/2 and
the Amiga on which ARexx is included as part of the operating system (2.0
and higher).

We'll look at the general format of a REXX program including the types of
statements and control structures; variables, expressions, and functions;
at using external libraries to extend the powers of REXX; and at the basic
tools to use REXX as an 'interprocess' medium to extend the functionality
of REXX-savvy programs.

By the end of this course, the student should be able to build useful
standalone programs using REXX and have a general understanding of how to
use REXX as a powerful macro language with other programs.

Although this course will focus on use of ARexx on the Amiga, its lessons
will also be useful those who wish to learn how REXX functions on other
platforms, including OS/2.

The student is expected to have a REXX interpreter or compiler and
ARexxGuide or another manual which includes a complete description of
instructions and built-in function calls. No other textbook is required.

Course Registration Fee: $55
8 weeks
Instructor: Robin Evans (R.EVANS6)
Course Meets: Sundays 9-11pm Eastern
First Class:  October 10

INFORMATION ABOUT CALC
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

     The Computer-Assisted Learning Center (CALC) is the nation's first
LIVE, online tutoring and education course center.   CALC opened its first
network campus in 1986 and is the established leader in online classroom
teaching. CALC's goal is to provide quality educational opportunities for
the entire family.  We do not have any age requirements for our tutoring or
for our courses. This makes for a large and varied student body.

     CALC has been carefully structured to make optimal use of the tools
available on GEnie which are already common to most of you.  Items, such as
software libraries, real-time conference rooms, and electronic bulletin
boards have all been transformed into highly effective teaching tools.
These tools provide greater individualized attention for students than in
many offline schools.  CALC is unique in the online educational market
because of its development of the real-time conference room as a classroom.
In this way, CALC teachers are in direct contact with their students.

     CALC provides a diverse blending of educational services which are
aimed at accommodating the needs of ALL involved in the educational
process: students, parents, and teachers.  You will discover many
educational opportunities here in CALC, such as:

* CALC TUTORING CENTER: Live tutoring/homework help
* CALC COURSE CENTER: Structured courses; fees charged
* Online QUIZZES For Fun

     All of CALC's educational services are provided by an experienced
staff of educators and professionals from across the nation.  Many teach
and work in their local schools during the day, and teach and tutor in CALC
in evenings and on weekends.  You will always find help with offline and
online studies, whether it be inside the online classrooms (RTCs)
face-to-face with a CALC teacher or within the closely monitored class
bulletin boards.

     We hope that you enjoy your experiences with CALC and that your entire
family will benefit from the learning opportunities provided here.  See you
around campus!

Margaret Morabito
Director of CALC

HOW TO REGISTER
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
		At any prompt, enter 'm175' or 'CALC'

		Choose item 7 to register for the class.

		This is the menu for the RT:


GEnie                        CALC                       Page  175
               Computer-Assisted Learning Center

 1.   CALC Bulletin Board
 2.   CALC Real-Time Classrooms (RTCs)
 3.   CALC Software Libraries
 4.   About CALC's Education Services
 5.   Announcements

 6.   CALC Course Catalog
 7.   CALC Course Registration
 8.   Student Survey

 9.   Learning Arcade
10.   Free LiveWire Download

Editor's Note:  There is an annual fee of $45 for CALC membership, which
entitles any member of a family to register for CALC courses.  The fee
for each course is additional, and ranges from $25 to $55.

@endnode

